    "Other research has found that detection accuracy can be significantly reduced by such attacks, including character-and word-level perturbations (Pu et al., 2023; Wang et al., 2024; Wu et al., 2024), paraphrasing (as a defense, rather than a generation strategy) (Sadasivan et al., 2023; Krishna et al., 2024; Masrour et al., 2025), and prompt-tuning (Kumarage et al., 2023b; Shi et al., 2024).",
    "as well as network characteristics (e.g., groups of accounts acting in a coordinated fashion) (Forrester et al., 2019; Cresci, 2020)."
